From Mike O'Connor Subject Re Motif vs Athena, etc In article A rgooch rp CSIRO AU Richard Gooch writes really involved there Many people using Linux like to stay at the cutting bleeding edge ie when kernel patches, C library or compiler patches come out, people like to rebuild their entire systems The prime requirement for all Linux software is that it is available under a GNU style public license Hence, Linux software uses either the Athena widgets or XView Individuals may write software requiring Motif, but I doubt it is widely adopted Shameless plug the Xaw d widgets make Athena a much nicer alternative than the stock MIT Athena code Mike Michael J O'Connor Internet Ford Motor Company, OPEO UUCP fmsrl opeo mjo Rotunda, Bldg Phone Dearborn, MI Fax